 V(T) 1 - T^2  = dt  L(t)
  
for the rolling tachyon. Without loss of generality we will
consider the D0-brane theory and take 
with  the D0-brane mass. Note that the tachyon field  used
here is not the same as that used in elsewhere in this paper but differs
by a field redefinition.
We will "derive" the tachyon potential
