Static solitons 

We now show the action, when including some
spatial directions, also contain  static solitonic
solutions which have the correct D-brane tension.

Solitonic solutions to  can be obtained by taking analytic
continuation  of the  solution ,
  T 2  = a x 2   .  
In the case of D-string, the above solutions correspond to a
periodic array of kinks and anti-kinks sitting at 
. As , the size of the kink becomes
infinitely thin and sharply localized.

The mass of the kink (or anti-kink)  can be obtained by
integration an half period () of , we find that
  M = _0 ^2    dx  V(T)  1 + T'^2 
 = 2 M_0 .
  
Note that this is independent of . Alternatively one can
imagine for  a single soliton is a configuration with
(see e.g.  , )
