where we have  approximated .
   From  we see that the deformation from the original D-string
configuration at  to the periodic array of kink-anti-kinks
does not cost energy, i.e.  it corresponds to a marginal
deformation. Note the ratio of tensions  matches precisely to that
between D-string and D0-brane given by string theory. In the
superstring theory we have an extra  in the ratios of
tensions due to the scaling mentioned before.


