C  Brane deformation due to closed string backgrounds  



In this appendix we will discuss a very simple example of the problem
of finding the deformation of a boundary state due to a closed
string deformation of the background.

Let us start with a flat spacetime. Let us consider a
D-brane in the 01 directions. Let us now deform the background
by deforming the metric by

ds^2 = ds^2_flat   + ( dx_1^2 - dx_3^2) e^ik x_2 +  k x_4  ,
 
where .
The deformation grows for large , but since the brane is localized
near , this is not important for our problem. We view
 simply as the leading term for the expansion of the
metric around .

This deformation will translate into the insertion of the vertex
operator

O (z,z) =
-  1 (X_1 X_1
- X_3 X_3)  e^ik X_2 +  k X_4 
 
The operator product expansion as  will be of the form

O (z,z)  2i z - z  V_1 +  ,
 
where the ellipsis indicate operators with other conformal weights and

V_1 =  1 2     ( i k  _n X_2 + k
 _n X_4 ) .
 
According to the arguments given in the text the boundary
deformation should obey

(L_0- 1)V_B = V_1  . 
This motivates us to look for solutions of the form

V_B = Y^2(X^0,X^1)  _n X_2 +
Y^4(X^0,X^1)  _n X_4  
where  implies

(-_0^2 + _1^2 ) Y^2 = 12  ik   ,         
(-_0^2 + _1^2 ) Y^4 = 12  k .
 
Note that  and  form a "logarithmic"
pair ,, .
(The fact that we get a complex answer in  is due
to the fact that we took a complex metric in , taking a real
metric we get  a real answer.)

Let us now compare with the results we would compute using the Born
Infeld action. The action can be expanded to lowest order
in small fluctuations  about  as

S = -Tdx^0dx^1 -g 
=- T dx^0 dx^1( 1+  1 2 ( Y^2)^2    +  1 2 ( Y^4)^2    +  1 2 
g_11 ) .
 
The equations of motion for this action become  once we
use  for the expression for .
We see that indeed the general CFT computation agrees with the answer
we expect based on the Born Infeld action. Note that since the
 is independent of  the solutions of  will
grow at infinity. This is in agreement with the expectation that
logarithmic divergences in CFT are cancelled by a change in the
long distance boundary conditions for the configuration.


It should be noted that if we give the metric deformation some
momentum along the brane. Then the operators in the OPE will not
generally have dimension one. It is not clear if we need to deform the
boundary state in this case since we do not get a logarithmic divergence.
  From the Born Infeld point of view we
would expect that we need to change the boundary state.

This discussion is closely related to the discussions
of brane recoil in ,, .




